description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join our established Therapy team in our Medical/HSEP and Frailty Therapy service. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant will be working with patients who are admitted to the wards with medical conditions. You will work closely with experienced physiotherapists and occupational therapists to support and assist patients with their rehabilitation programme and to enable them to be discharged safely from hospital. As well as working jointly with therapists, you will also have the opportunity to work with patients on an individual basis. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Support Worker role involves assisting patients with self-care tasks such as washing/dressing, activities of daily living, mobility and exercise programmes. The role will also involve delivering therapy equipment in the local area and supporting with home visits with the therapists. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for an individual who demonstrates an enthusiastic and flexible approach to their work, and who is motivated to provide excellent care for our patients and to help them achieve their maximum functional ability. Strong communication skills and the ability to work as part of a multi-disciplinary team are essential for this position.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are committed to supporting development of staff through training, supervision, joint sessions with therapists and appraisal. We have an established competency programme and you will be supported to work through these. Competencies include general rehab tasks as well as increasing knowledge about medical conditions. Therapies provide a 7 day therapy service, and any successful applicant will be expected to participate in the rota.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This advert will close once sufficient numbers of suitable applications have been received, therefore it is advisable to apply promptly if you are interested in the post. We welcome applications from candidates interested in a flexible working pattern/hours. This must be raised at interview to be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Claire Cushen&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Clinical Lead Medical HSEP&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: claire.cushen@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 02082164585&lt;/p&gt;
